  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Cut the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small florets, discard the stem and leaves</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1632736876576-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1632736876576-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1632736876576-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1632736876576-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1632736876576-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632736888975-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632736888975-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632736888975-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632736888975-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632736888975-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Rinse the <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under<strong> cold running water</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>in half</p>",
